<section class="overview" id="philmont">
  <h2>Philmont Scout Ranch</h2>
  <p><strong>Location:</strong> Cimarron, New Mexico</p>
  <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Backpacking at altitude</p>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Programs</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>12-Day Trek — Classic Philmont experience</li>
      <li>9-Day Trek — Condensed adventure</li>
      <li>7-Day Trek — Short but epic</li>
      <li>Cavalcade — Horseback riding option</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Requirements</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>14 years old OR 8th grade graduate (13 with grade completion)</li>
      <li>Complete Physical Exam (Part C of health form)</li>
      <li>Strong cardiovascular fitness</li>
      <li>Backpacking experience recommended</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What to Expect</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>6,000-12,000 ft elevation</li>
      <li>50-100+ miles hiking</li>
      <li>Heavy pack (45-50 lbs typical)</li>
      <li>Remote backcountry camping</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cost</h3>
    <p>~$850-1,200 per person (2025-2026 rates)</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="overview" id="northern-tier">
  <h2>Northern Tier</h2>
  <p><strong>Location:</strong> Ely, Minnesota (plus bases in Canada)</p>
  <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Wilderness canoeing and cold weather camping</p>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Programs</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Lone Voyage — 7 nights, $850, ages 14+</li>
      <li>Grand Portage — 10 days, $895, 115 miles + 8-mile portage</li>
      <li>Okpik Winter — Cold weather camping, ~$62/day</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Requirements</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>14 years old OR 8th grade graduate (13 with grade completion)</li>
      <li>Strong swimming ability (swim test required)</li>
      <li>Comfortable in wilderness settings</li>
      <li>Cold weather tolerance for winter programs</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What to Expect</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>50-150 miles paddling</li>
      <li>Boundary Waters wilderness</li>
      <li>Portaging canoes and gear</li>
      <li>Weather-dependent challenges</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cost</h3>
    <p>~$850-950 for individual programs, ~$54-62/person/day</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="overview" id="sea-base">
  <h2>Florida Sea Base</h2>
  <p><strong>Location:</strong> Florida Keys (and Bahamas)</p>
  <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Water-based adventures</p>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Programs</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Reef — snorkeling and island camping</li>
      <li>Scuba — certified scuba diving</li>
      <li>Out Island — sailing and camping</li>
      <li>Bahamas — island-hopping adventure</li>
      <li>St. Thomas — Caribbean exploration</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Requirements</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>13 years old (by arrival date)</li>
      <li>BSA Swimmer classification</li>
      <li>No insulin-dependent diabetes, asthma, or seizures (certain restrictions)</li>
      <li>140/90 max BP, 295 lbs weight limit</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What to Expect</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Tropical marine environments</li>
      <li>Sailing, snorkeling, scuba</li>
      <li>Island camping</li>
      <li>Warm weather, water activities</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cost</h3>
    <p>~$550-750+ per person (varies by program)</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="overview" id="summit">
  <h2>Summit Bechtel Reserve</h2>
  <p><strong>Location:</strong> Mount Hope, West Virginia</p>
  <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Activity sampler</p>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Programs</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Summit Experience — 6-day sampler</li>
      <li>Focused Programs — dive deep into specific activities</li>
      <li>Advanced Programs — for returning crews</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Activities</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Mountain biking and BMX</li>
      <li>Rock climbing and high ropes</li>
      <li>Whitewater rafting and kayaking</li>
      <li>Shooting sports (archery, rifle, shotgun)</li>
      <li>Challenge courses and ziplines</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Requirements</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Typically 14+ for high adventure programs</li>
      <li>Moderate fitness</li>
      <li>5-7 miles walking daily on uneven terrain</li>
      <li>Heat tolerance (can reach 100°F index)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cost</h3>
    <p>~$450-600 per person (2025 rates)</p>
  </div>
</section>

